There are chaotic scenes at the Pan-African Parliament (PAP) in Midrand, Johannesburg. Members of the PAP have been seen on visuals from the facility in what appears to be a dispute over a ballot box. A voice can be heard calling for police to be called to the PAP while voting for the PAP leadership has been disrupted. Scenes at the Pan African Parliament:  Last week, members in Parliament were engaged in a fierce debate over the issue of rotational leadership instead of direct elections. The vote, which had been scheduled for last Thursday, was abandoned after a staff member tested positive for COVID-19. Pan-African Parliament | Contestation of views over-rotation of regions for leadership of parliament  MEDIA STATEMENT pic.twitter.com/gXrMyLOM31 â€” PanAfricanParliament (@AfrikParliament) May 27, 2021 